<subSubSection id="0AC35C68BEA337C0B3E26AF0C7D18E26" lastPageId="126" lastPageNumber="127" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="description">
<paragraph id="43512F829A96BC498ECAF8279778795E" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DDC4B5BA721289BFB6045581A49A6B00" lastPageId="126" lastPageNumber="127" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
Undershrub forming a small bush up to 40 cm high and 60 cm wide; stems from a deep woody taproot, many, ascending, rigid, green, glabrous, sometimes spinescent at the tips, weakly divaricate. Leaves sessile, 1.7-2.5 
<normalizedToken id="9131EADBCB70308120D745F4F6072E45" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.4 
<pageBreakToken id="F3F55F423F6FCF2930CFB2B317C98C31" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" start="start">cm</pageBreakToken>
, lanceolate or linear-lanceolate, glabrous, acute or acuminate, margin entire, base truncate to obscurely auriculate. Inflorescence of few-flowered, axillary, pedunculate, hirsute heads; peduncles 1.5-4.5(-8) cm, rigid, woody; bracteoles 5-12 
<normalizedToken id="F064471C201394B13001C28372D5DD12" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 mm, very variable in size, linear or lanceolate, acute; pedicels 1-2 mm, often bent at a sharp angle to the peduncle; sepals 8-9 
<normalizedToken id="04C9F9C96B3D8CBFF1D026E056D10DE1" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
2-2.5 mm, ovate, acuminate, villous; corolla 1.3-2.1 cm, usually white, sometimes pinkish, shallowly lobed, the midpetaline bands ending in teeth, pubescent, sometimes darker pink; ovary glabrous; style glabrous, divided c. 5.5 mm above the base, stigmas 1-1.25 mm, elliptic. Capsule glabrous; 1-2-seeded; seeds tuberculate, glabrous. [
